Package: quicR
Title: RT-QuIC Data Formatting and Analysis
Version: 2.1.0
Authors@R: person( given = "Gage", family = "Rowden", email =
        "gage.rowden1145@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment =
        c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7517-0480") )
Description: Designed for the curation and analysis of data generated
        from real-time quaking-induced conversion (RT-QuIC) assays
        first described by Atarashi et al. (2011)
        <doi:10.1038/nm.2294>. 'quicR' calculates useful metrics such
        as maxpoint ratio: Rowden et al. (2023)
        <doi:10.1099/vir.0.069906-0>; time-to-threshold: Shi et al.
        (2013) <doi:10.1186/2051-5960-1-44>; and maximum slope.
        Integration with the output from plate readers allows for
        seamless input of raw data into the R environment.
Imports: dplyr, ggplot2, janitor, openxlsx, purrr, readxl, reshape2,
        slider, stats, stringr, tidyr
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
